 C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104aym1665702709149.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/aym1665702709149.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/aym1665702709149.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"aym1665702709149\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Classification\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body refbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Interface definition for a variable or operation parameter with <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Data\n         Type</span>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">Handle</code> or <code class=\"ph codeph\">XMLStream</code>. </p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"aym1665702709149__section_udm_fjs_cxb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d480554e60\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"aym1665702709149__p_d110666e1_d110667e1_d110668e1\">If the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Data Type</span> is\n               <code class=\"ph codeph\">XMLStream</code>, specify the DTD for the data contents.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"aym1665702709149__p_d110669e1_d110670e1_d110671e1\">If the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Data Type</span> is\n               <code class=\"ph codeph\">Handle</code>, specify the component signature that the handle points\n            to.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"aym1665702709149__section_gtg_gjs_cxb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d480554e84\">Applies to</h2>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"aym1665702709149__ul_ym4_hjs_cxb\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"aym1665702709149__li_d42710e1_d42711e1_d42712e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"luz1665702709079.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/luz1665702709079.html\" title=\"A Global Variable is a Development Object that defines a typed variable that can be accessed by all ProcScript in the application.\">Global Variable</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"aym1665702709149__li_d42713e1_d42714e1_d42715e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"jha1665702714162.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/jha1665702714162.html\" title=\"A Signature Parameter is a Development Object that describes an argument that can be passed in or out of an operation.\">Signature Parameter</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/tzf1665702562469.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Signatures</a><p>A Uniface signature describes the remote interface of a component. The interface enables other components to address the component without knowing anything about the implementation. This allows components of different origin to communicate through their respective interfaces.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3612031\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3612031\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Classification Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 11, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Classification Interface definition for a variable or operation parameter with Data Type Handle or XMLStream . Description If the Data Type is XMLStream , specify the DTD for the data contents. If the Data Type is Handle , specify the component signature that the handle points to. Applies to Global Variable Signature Parameter Related Links Signatures A Uniface signature describes the remote interface of a component. The interface enables other components to address the component without knowing anything about the implementation. This allows components of different origin to communicate through their respective interfaces. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}